description: Arsenal are unbeaten in their five home matches in European competitions against PSV, the most home games theyve played against an opponent in European competition without ever losing. title: Real Madrid vs Atletico Madrid - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Round of 16 - 1st Leg
description: This will be the 10th meeting between Real and Atletico Madrid in the European Cup/UEFA Champions League; the joint-most between teams from the same nation, along with Chelsea versus Liverpool. Real Madrid and Atletico Madrid have faced each other in the knockout stages of the European Cup/UEFA Champions League in five previous seasons, with Los Blancos progressing/winning on all five occasions.

title: AZ Alkmaar vs Tottenham Hotspur - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - R16 - 1st Leg

Spurs have won seven of their last 11 major European matches against Dutch sides, with this their first knockout meeting since beating Ajax 3-2 in May 2019 in the second leg of the UEFA Champions League semi-final to reach the final.

title: Roma vs Athletic Club - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - R16 - 1st Leg

title: Feyenoord vs Internazionale - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Round of 16 - 1st Leg
description: This will be just the third meeting between Feyenoord and Internazionale in major European competition, with the Dutch side winning 3-2 on aggregate in the pair’s prior UEFA Cup semi-final tie during the 2001-02 season. Feyenoord have lost just one of their 12 home games in European competition against Italian sides, with the exception coming in a 2-1 defeat to Roma during the 2014-15 UEFA Europa League.

title: Benfica vs Barcelona - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Round of 16 - 1st Leg
description: Benfica and Barcelona have faced each other on 10 previous occasions in the European Cup/UEFA Champions League, with the 11th making it the joint-most times Benfica have faced an opponent across the two competitions. Benfica and Barcelona have already met in the UEFA Champions League this season, with nine goals being scored in an eventual 5-4 win for Barcelona. Of the 40 times that Benfica have scored 4+ goals in a European home match, that’s the only occasion when they’ve ever failed to win.

title: Ajax vs Eintracht Frankfurt - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - R16 - 1st Leg
description: This will be the first ever meeting between Ajax and Eintracht Frankfurt with the Dutch side losing just one of their previous 21 home matches against German opposition in major European competition, a 1-4 loss to Borussia Dortmund in the group stage of the UEFA Champions League in 2012-13. Eintracht Frankfurt have progressed from each of their previous two knockout ties against Dutch opposition in major European competition, however they did lose both away games in those ties.

Lazio have won three of their last four away games in major European competition, as many as in their previous 25 matches.

title: Bayern Munchen vs Bayer Leverkusen - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Round of 16 - 1st Leg

Bayern Munich won their last match against German opposition in the UEFA Champions League against Borussia Dortmund in the 2012-13 final, whilst Bayer Leverkusen last faced German opposition in the 2007-08 UEFA Cup, when they were defeated 3-2 by Hamburger SV. Under Xabi Alonso, Bayer Leverkusen are unbeaten in their six matches against Bayern Munich across all competitions. They’ve kept a clean sheet in three of their last four against them, after not keeping any in their previous 15 games against Bayern beforehand.

Liverpool and Paris Saint-Germain will face each other in the knockout stages of a major European competition for the first time since meeting in the semi-final of the Cup Winners’ Cup in 1996-97, with the Parisians progressing to the final following a 3-2 aggregate victory.
